article.headline: ETSU 82, Chattanooga 70
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- Kevin Tiggs scored a game-high 32 points to lead East Tennessee State to an 82-70 win against in-state foe Chattanooga on Wednesday night. Courtney Pigram scored 24 points for the Buccaneers (7-3), and Mike Smith added 10. Pigram also dished out seven assists and hit six 3-pointers. Stephen McDowell scored 28 points to lead the Mocs (1-7), and Nicchaeus Doaks and Ty Patterson added 10 apiece. Khalil Hartwell notched a game-high 10 rebounds, and McDowell also hit six shots from beyond the arc. The teams were tied at 41-all at the break, but the Buccaneers went on a 13-4 run to start the second half and led the rest of the way. The Buccaneers outscored the Mocs in the paint 38-14 in the win.
